{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6a63a91f-0ed9-4213-a3a1-9a041b3178b8","content":"This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10 MAUI, Android runs in **edge-to-edge** mode by default, which makes the deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` flag (that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` relied on) stop working.\n\nThe modern fix is to react to **keyboard window insets** on Android. In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Android.Views;\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Platform;\n\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity\n{\n    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n    {\n        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(\n            Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());\n    }\n\n    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n    {\n        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(\n            Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n        {\n            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n            var barInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());\n\n            v.SetPadding(\n                barInsets.Left,\n                barInsets.Top,\n                barInsets.Right,\n                Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, barInsets.Bottom));\n\n            return insets;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAlso ensure your `AndroidManifest.xml` activity still has:\n\n```xml\nandroid:windowSoftInputMode=\"adjustResize\"\n```\n\n**Why this works:** Instead of relying on the removed resize behavior, you listen for IME (keyboard) insets directly and add bottom padding equal to the keyboard height. When the keyboard opens, the bottom padding pushes your input bar up; when it closes, padding returns to normal.\n\n**Tip:** You can remove any old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` calls from your MAUI code — they're no longer needed with this approach.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7942b8e5-71c9-49da-b011-59f496f51c83","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the text input at the bottom of the screen. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` worked in .NET 9 but doesn't work in .NET 10. This is a known breaking change in .NET MAUI / Android.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n\nIn .NET MAUI for .NET 9 (and earlier), on Android, you could use `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` to make the layout resize when the soft keyboard appears. However, `Resize` was deprecated in Android API 30+ and in .NET 10 MAUI, this API was removed or no longer functions.\n\n\nThe modern approach in .NET 10 is to use edge-to-edge mode with `WindowInsets` to handle keyboard visibility, since `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` itself was deprecated by Android. I should recommend using `KeyboardPadding` or listening to keyboard insets instead. I don't have direct access to the latest documentation, but based on what I know about .NET MAUI 10's edge-to-edge defaults on Android, the modern approach involves either using the `KeyboardPadding` attached property or properly handling IME insets through the manifest configuration.\n\nFor .NET 10 specifically, setting `android:windowSoftInputMode=\"adjustResize\"` in the AndroidManifest.xml still works for basic scenarios, but the recommended pattern now uses `ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` to detect keyboard insets and adjust padding dynamically, or leveraging MAUI's built-in support for this.\n\nWriting platform-specific code... I'm realizing that in .NET MAUI 10, edge-to-edge rendering is enabled by default on Android, which means `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works as it did before since it relied on deprecated Android behavior. The proper solution is to manually handle keyboard insets on the Android platform side instead.","outputTokens":2014,"requestId":"1120:1FF93E:C71FA1:E912F8:69FE887B"},"id":"4fb1323b-1c55-4570-9eaa-97890447fbad","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:06:40.868Z","parentId":"16f50de9-735e-4380-8a90-ed94eceeeb8b"}
